snippet.textDisplay: It does make a difference - only the ref can stop the fight. Despite the towel being thrown in, the Ref has to agree with the towel throw. In the fight, you can see from round 4 onwards that ref is often looking at Wilder carefully. As soon as the towel came in, he didn’t think twice. He was ready to stop it himself within a few more seconds imo. As tyson said in the post fight interview, he was smothering his own work against the ropes by stepping in too closely. If he’d kept that distance and unloaded without falling into him and the clinch, ref would’ve stopped it in round 5 imo.
